{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2e97f459-cf26-4a3b-85f5-02e83cc89ba3","content":"With xUnit.net v3 + MTP, the VSTest filter syntax (`--filter`) is replaced by the `--filter` flag using **MTP filter expressions**, which have different operators:\n\n**Old (VSTest / xUnit v2):**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n**New (MTP / xUnit v3):**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nKey differences:\n| VSTest | MTP |\n|--------|-----|\n| `&` | `and` |\n| `\\|` | `or` |\n| `!` | `not` |\n| `~` (contains) | `~` (still works) |\n| `=` (equals) | `=` (still works) |\n\nThe operators become **words** (`and`, `or`, `not`) instead of symbols. The property names and match operators (`~`, `=`) remain the same. xUnit v3 still surfaces `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` as a `Category` filter property, so that part is unchanged.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5f736d46-d657-4e80-9ec9-ae8d3706c729","outputTokens":281,"requestId":"BD01:39A6CA:1D3E433:20F4169:6A07C591"},"id":"26e64120-7d11-4858-be57-c3bdae5765df","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:17:12.131Z","parentId":"99c256e4-df8b-4882-8d42-3a9a373c140a"}
